item.title: Cohesive-zone model
item.description: Solid-state batteries are promising candidates for high-energy density applications, like powering electric cars. The battery materials, however, mechanically degrade with continuous usage. This degradation limits interfacial kinetics and lowers the battery power-density. A cohesive-zone model is used to investigate the electro-chemo-mechanical coupling that leads to fracture and delamination in solid-state batteries. Collaborators: Dorthe Ravnsbaek SDU, Denmark                           Giovanna Bucci Bosch, USA                           W. Craig Carter Massachusetts Insitute of Technology, USA                           Yet-Ming Chiang Massachusetts Insitute of Technology, USA
